## CH01. Trade-Offs in Data Systems Architecture

- Five functionalities of common applications
    - Store data → Databases
    - Remember the result of an expensive operation → Caches
    - Search data by keyword → Search indexes
    - Handle evens → Stream processing
    - Periodically crunch large amount of data → Batch processing
    
    ⇒ But, there are various approaches for each of them
- Operational vs Analytics system
    - Operational systems read and modify the data based on the action performed by users
        - known as OLTP (Online Transaction Processing)
        - “Systems of Record” (Source of truth)
    - Analytics system only read the data and process the data for analytics needs
        - known as OLAP (Online Analytical Processing)
        - uses Data Warehouse as an seperate database processed by ETL (Extract-Transform-Load)
        - “Derived data systems”
- Cloud vs Self-Hosting